{"title": "Missing escape of HTML entities in Handlebars template compilation", "summary": "  As a templating engine, Handlebars generates HTML markup dynamically. Setting `noEscape` to true disables escaping HTML entities within the template output itself.  This is a security risk as it could lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities if the template is from an untrusted source. ", "description": "\n\nAs a templating engine, Handlebars generates HTML markup dynamically.\nSetting `noEscape` to true disables escaping HTML entities within the template output itself.\n\nThis is a security risk as it could lead to Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities if\nthe template is from an untrusted source.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Do not set `noEscape` to true when compiling Handlebars templates\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-80"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/javascript_lang_handlebars_no_escape"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}